{title:Rokutousei No Yoru}
{artist:Aimer}

Adapted from: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=n5jv_zKm3Uo

I fell in love with this song, and after seeing the YouTuber above perform an amazing acoustic
version, I set out to lay down some rough chords. She included some chords in her video 
description, but I tabbed directly from the video, and I like these chords better. This song 
is in 4/4 time, so in the intro and the interludes, each backslash indicates the end of a 4-beat 
measure. If you're confused, you can ask me or watch the video, which will give you the 
strumming pattern.

[EDIT] There's two funky chords that I've nicknamed G1 and G2 (even though they're most 
likely not G chords). I also use Bm here instead of Bm7, but both sound fine.

--------------------------------------------------------------

Tuning: Standard EADGBe

G1  3|3|2|0|0|0
G2  3|3|2|0|0|1 
Bb  1|1|3|3|2|1 

Capo 1

--------------

